    {
      "id": "887d9f5ae7dd74f81589f38c7f59c4f5a395d61a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 17:55:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPKG_CHECK_MODULES is considered 'standard'. Its really broken?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3af1b9ecaad844265ce16d32d7da07350431b46b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 17:57:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI wonder if something like this will fix the problem?\n\nPKG_CHECK_MODULES(X11, x11 > 1.6.4, [AC_DEFINE(HAVE_X11)], [:])",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "c7002a5c2069f3de0d217bf73d88f755525b5fed",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 18:19:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI could add a fixes line. But, the change is so small that it probably not worth back-porting. The functionality is identical. It's a developer QoL fix.\n\nEvery couple months I run into this warning, and spend a lot of time debugging before realize pkg-config is missing. The issue can't be fixed using PKG_CHECK_MODULES, since pkg-config provides that macro. If you don't have it, you get arcane errors when autotools explodes.\n\nThis post (https://stackoverflow.com/questions/10220946/pkg-check-modules-considered-harmful) helped me understand why this strange behavior happens. I'm open to other ideas, as long as configure outputs sane errors.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ca3b2d286a0fd75ae5c33b7bd454c2c8d87fe976",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 683,
        "name": "jenkins",
        "email": "devops@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jenkins",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 18:33:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified-1\n\nBuild Failed \n\nhttps://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/96359/ : FAILURE",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2f7e93e850303a1f59bfcb013d0345e7df734ab3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 18:41:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPKG_CHECK_MODULES does more than just check. It sets up the CFLAGS and LIBS settings. This patch still doesn't deal with the missing pkg-config. \n\nHow about something like this:\n\ndiff --git a/configure.ac b/configure.ac\nindex 7c96386..4000a38 100644\n--- a/configure.ac\n+++ b/configure.ac\n@@ -29,6 +29,7 @@ AC_PROG_MKDIR_P\n AC_PATH_PROG(FLEX, flex)\n AC_PATH_PROG(BISON, bison)\n AC_PATH_PROG(RPMBUILD, rpmbuild)\n+AC_PATH_PROG(PKGCONF, pkg-config)\n\n LUSTRE_VERSION_CPP_MACROS\n LB_CONFIGURE\ndiff --git a/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4 b/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4\nindex 84a2b0d..58e1fe6 100644\n--- a/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4\n+++ b/lnet/autoconf/lustre-lnet.m4\n@@ -1211,6 +1211,9 @@ LB_CHECK_FILE([$GDS_PATH/nvfs-dma.h],\n )\n\n # lnet/utils/lnetconfig/liblnetconfig_netlink.c\n+AS_IF([test \"x$PKGCONF\" = \"x\"],\n+       [AC_MSG_ERROR([pkg-config package is required to build lustre libraries])])\n+\n AS_IF([test \"x$enable_dist\" = xno], [\n        PKG_CHECK_MODULES(LIBNL3, [libnl-genl-3.0 >= 3.1])\n ])",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b3f19b2f37f1a18bc18f84c97fd8781f0de1bda7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2023-07-19 19:06:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThat seems reasonable. I uninstalled pkg-config and it output a warning. I'll update the patch to the one you gave. Thanks for the help.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
